The braced { js`…` } embedded-literal attribute form round-trips its braces
(canonicalized tight). Braces are preserved because on a component tag a braced
literal binds a declared prop while the bare form falls through to the Attrs
bag — stripping them would change the meaning. The bare form stays bare.
Interpolation-hole whitespace is normalized either way.

-- input.gsx --
package p

component C(id string) {
	<Widget Handler={ js`open(@{ id })` } data-x=js`bare(@{id})`/>
}
-- fmt.golden --
package p

component C(id string) {
	<Widget Handler={js`open(@{id})`} data-x=js`bare(@{id})`/>
}
